Uganda Bourse Re-Admits National Insurance, Monitor Reports

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-09-08T08:02:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/uganda-bourse-re-admits-national-insurance-monitor-reports.html
Uganda’s stock market lifted a
trading ban on  National Insurance Corp. (NIC)  after it published
audited accounts, the  Daily Monitor reported , citing Joseph Kitamirike, the exchange’s chief executive.  The shares resumed trading yesterday after the company
published 2010 results on Aug. 3 and earnings for the six months
through June on Sept. 1, the Kampala-based newspaper said.  National Insurance is a unit of Lagos, Nigeria-based
Industrial and General Insurance Plc, which acquired a
controlling stake from the Ugandan government in 2005.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Johannesburg at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 